Author: cryptopreacher
Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: Hello MarcusA,  Let us go point by point again:  1. We are not kidding, we have better things to do than spam our own telegram chat with accounts. 2. Regarding the roadmap, that iteration is September, October, November (3 months). As you are probably aware, it is only 2nd of November. 3. The main page starts correctly, only when you refresh the page, it doesn't know how to proceed; that is a issue because nginx not being configured to do so - which we are aware of since the day we deployed it, so on this side you can expect everything to be fine with the new deployment - we will probably setup the configuration on nginx or switch to nodejs; there is no apache being involved in our arhitecture 4. Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: !!! Go Help Fund SCAM !!! http://a.radikal.ru/a12/1810/16/8efb1d798449.jpg  So Friends, recently on coinmarketcap.com a HELP token from the go help fund command was added. This token interested me and I decided to figure out what he is the whole project.. Let's start with you a careful study of this ambitious project from go help fund.. The project with careful consideration was very difficult and in its own amazing. Why amazing? Yes, because wherever you look, whatever you start to study carefully, everywhere there is only lies and deception, which in principle is the essence of this "miracle project". But first things first..  1. Let's start with the office address listed on the team's website: Fundac Sf. Teodor, nr. 1, Iasi, Romania, open Google maps.. And what we see. This is College! http://a.radikal.ru/a06/1810/ed/6585898813be.jpg What's this bullshit about a College office? No signs of the project, no signs, I wonder, and the College administration is aware that in their building are rented and used premises for offices?? Yes, it's just COLLEGE and that's our first conclusion: GO HELP FUND SCAM!!!  2. Let's go ahead and see a group of telegrams and immediately see that not live people are added there, but bots. "deleted accounts" at every step, see for yourself and everything will become clear – you will see that  GO HELP FUND SCAM!!! https://t.me/gohelpfund http://d.radikal.ru/d05/1810/32/3baf0665371f.jpg  http://b.radikal.ru/b24/1810/1b/55e1a9200155.jpg  http://b.radikal.ru/b33/1810/30/8aa584d46234.jpg  http://d.radikal.ru/d02/1810/ee/f88a2e1b8627.jpg  3. Go on.. And on coinmarketcap.com we see that this strange token, which in truth already seems doubtful to us, is traded on two exchanges. This mercatox.com and stellar port.io if mercatox paired with BTC, we still see some trades or at least the created visibility of these trades-then, on stellarport.io we only see this: http://b.radikal.ru/b00/1810/02/864dd8932042.jpg - and again conclusion: GO HELP FUND SCAM!!!  4. Well.. Now it's time to go to the official website https://gohelpfund.com/ where except deranged whitepaper https://gohelpfund.com/assets/whitepaper.pdf Why then are these well-known and respected of the exchange as bitrix, balance, hitbtc, ku, coin, cryptobia.co.nz But these exchanges not traded the token for this command. And again we are misled – and again the conclusion: GO HELP FUND SCAM!!! https://gohelpfund.com/ http://a.radikal.ru/a40/1810/55/719ae6be7a4a.jpg  5. And now the most interesting.. The team has been working on the project since may 2017 and even released a beta platform... Maybe we're not talking about the fact that this project is a real Scam? Let's look at what these guys have been working on for so long and what the team has provided us as this very beta platform that they have been working on.. http://beta.gohelpfund.com/ Well at first glance it looks quite cute.. http://c.radikal.ru/c08/1810/a6/3f6c7efb89a9.jpg Let's look a little closer and rewind the page down..  And what we see.. http://a.radikal.ru/a30/1810/cd/9cdc03fd986b.jpg Let's see what is this beta platform on which the team has been working for so long.? Yes, this is the easiest site that any of my students will write in no more than an hour. There is a button to Create a fundraising company. Anything and anything.. But what about after the fundraising company is set up..? That's it! The help button doesn't work! This beta platform is just a real shame! http://a.radikal.ru/a28/1810/82/3293bdca001f.jpg And this is what the team gave us as a beta platform? This, in principle, impossible to articulate! At all! No way! It's pure deception! Conclusion: GO HELP FUND SCAM!!! ----- Friends! Stay away from go help fund and never mess with these scams! ----- Good luck to everyone and have a nice day, friends!

Author: cryptopreacher
Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: Dear community,  In the past month we have been researching and discussing with various exchanges and reached a consensus. We have taken multiple factors in consideration such as experience based on the history and running time, reputation, great community with a lot of active members, chatbox, and last but not least a lot of potential to grow (UI/UX and more).  Secondly, due to the fact that is in the CoinMarketCap’s Top 100 Exchanges and it has a real volume and most relevant for us for the new coins/tokens added.  https://mercatox.com/news/help-added  Meanwhile, we have decided to create an weekly announcement(each Friday) with all the progress made during our sprints using the Agile methodology (Scrum in our case), among other updates.  Thank you,  GoHelpFund Team   https://medium.com/@gohelpfund/our-first-exchange-mercatox-4f1e6f71ac58

Author: cryptopreacher
Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: Dear community,  We have been working on the platform using the scrum methodology, with releases every 2 weeks (sprint duration). Currently we are in the middle of the sprint and our first release will be at the end of the month.  Meanwhile, we are in discussions with exchanges and we will most likely get listed on a new one, more information on that as soon as it's available. On the same topic, we are engaged with strategies for reaching on coinmarketcap.com and other similar coin aggregators.  On the technical side, we have migrated our infrastructure to a new AWS clean environment, got an iOS invision prototype ready for display on our website, and some other updates which will be available by the end of the sprint.  Regarding online presence, we have discussed and agreed on a strategy for posting news and updates more frequently, such as weekly and sometimes daily; added a chat bot to prevent spam on our Telegram channel, our sub-reddit page will be released soon enough; created a new discord channel, which can be accessed via our website in the bottom navigation bar, and last but not least refactored our website after the token sale with a fresh user interface.  On the HELP structure aspect, we are in the phase of our last air-drop, which is the one for sale participants and we are currently discussing a burning strategy for our excess funds and a giveaway/air-drop strategy for our bounty fund to increase our community even further.  Last but not least, we would like to thank the community for the support and say that we value the feedback received, which we discuss it in every meeting, because we can analyse it objectively and see what needs to be improved and transfer these points into real actions within our development and marketing cycle.

Author: cryptopreacher
Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: Dear community,  We have deployed the invision prototype for our iOS application, on our website, and it can be accesed via the home section. You can interact with the mockup and see a preview of our upcoming Beta release in which you can participate if you have an iPhone device via the TestFlight application, through an invite from us; more information on this will be available on the given time.  On the Devops & Backend side, we have finished an important topic of research that will benefit our platform greatly on the mid to long term: fine-grained microservice architectures. In the age of on-demand virtualization, infrastructure automation, continuous delivery, systems at scale and small autonomous teams, it is vital that the fundamental design of our platform must provide strategic key benefits such as technology heterogeneity, resilience, scaling, ease of deployment, organizational alignment, composability and more; for a more detailed report, check out our medium blog for the upcoming article.  Last but not least, we have finished distributing the air-drop bonus for the token sale holders, therefore stay tuned for the upcoming token burn strategy.

Author: cryptopreacher
Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: Hello people,  We would like to thank everybody who participated in our Token Pre-Sale, thus we have raised successfully $125,000 which was our pre-sale cap. Secondly, we listen and read everything you say on our social media, slack chat, intercom chat and emails, thus the feedback received was processed and the following actions will be taken:  - Migration from slack to telegram, as the main way of communicating with the community. - Detailed team member descriptions, together with video presentations and company meetings. - Live interviews/pod-casts for investors, where we will present our platform/team/vision. - Begin massive advertising/marketing on CoinMarketcap, CoinTelegraph, CoinSchedule, IcoAlert and other important websites. - Implement additional features on the Personal Dashboard, e.g. view the number of tokens bought and more - Expand/Complete our team on missing positions (PR/Marketing/Advisors/...) - Include expanded technical details in the white-paper - Implement professional website for our company domain - Improve current personal dashboard on the UI/UX part - Continue to be as transparent as possible, and as quick to respond on intercom chat as before  Last but not least, I would like to thank the people that are currently participating in our bounty campaign and remind that the registration is still opened, more details on the 'Bounty' medium link from our website. The upcoming Token Sale will start on 24th of February, 18:00 UTC+2.

Author: cryptopreacher
Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: We would like to make an important announcement that will benefit everybody, from investors to core team members.  First of all, let me mention that we did not have prior experience with ICOs, but only from our analysis done on other ICOs, we have learned a lot of valuable aspects regarding the structure of an ICO, UI/UX and most importantly advertising.  After an objective analysis, we have concluded that the best option is to do a rebranding which will benefit both investors like you and founders like us because it will incentivize us to work full time on the platform.  To resume it in a phrase, we will be rebranding the coin/platform into a single entity: platform+coin  > 'Go Help Fund' - platform and token name with the token symbol being 'HELP' ( referred as HELP tokens)  > Full professional redesign of the website and integration to invest with other options for the crowdsale (such as BTC, LTC, BCH, and more)  > Token Pre-Sale equivalent of $125,000 : - full details will be released soon  > Token Sale equivalent of $475,000: - full details will be released soon  > The Token Pre-Sale will take place in January. Stay tuned for more updates!

Author: cryptopreacher
Title: [ANN] GoHelpFund - HELP Coin [Coinmarketcap][Exchanges][Master Nodes] and more
Body: Hello people,  We have an important update related to the Initial Coin Offering that will benefit everyone, from investors to members and bounty hunters. We changed the structure as it follows:  - ICO Period: Nov 17th 18:00 UTC to Dec 1st 18:00 UTC (2 weeks)  - Total coins issued: 12,000,000 (13,333 ETH or ~$4,000,000)  - ICO coins: 9,000,000 (10,000 ETH or ~$3,000,000)  - Founders/Team members: 2,400,000 (2,666 ETH or ~$800,000)  [locked for 2 years, following a progressive unlock of another 2 years to ensure a healthy transition into the market]  - Bounty Campaign: 600,000 (666 ETH or ~$200,000) [remaining coins will be burned among with the unsold coins]  - Conversion rate: 900 HOLY = 1 ETH (~$0.3/coin)  All related resources (Website, Whitepaper, etc.) have been updated. We will also begin soon our bounty campaign where we will create a separate thread from this one. Stay tuned for more news!  Cheers, CryptoPreacher
